<br>
&quot;Ender's Shadow&quot; is a book written to take place at the same time as &quot;Ender's Game&quot; but focuses on a different character (Bean).<br>
<br>
In most people's opinions, if you like Ender's game, but did not like the sequels, you will enjoy the &quot;Ender's Shadow&quot; series.<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre>       Two Story Lines:
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Ender</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->                    <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Bean</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->

Ender's Game             Ender's Shadow
Speaker for the Dead     Shadow of the Hegemon
Xenocide                 Shadow Puppets
Children of the mind

Misc: First Meetings</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END-->Note that Shadow of the Hegemon, unlike Ender's Shadow, does not take place at the same time as Speaker for the Dead. Chronologically, Ender and Bean's timelines diverge. I hope that answers your question.<br>
