<br>
Ender's Game however is absolutely near the top of any &quot;mandatory reading&quot; books for anyone.  I do like Wolfgang Peterson as a director, but this is another case of a movie that can't help but live up to the book.  Even though that's said every time a movie is made from a book, I really do think it's even moreso here.  Especially since a big part of reading the book for the first time was the ending.  That won't be a surprise for the movie, at least for most.  I don't know, I just can't see how it'll transfer well to the big screen, especially with a vast majority of the characters in the story being children.  <br>
<br>
At the very least if you have never read Ender's Game do so.  You don't have to read any of the other books, it stands above all of them on its own.  <p>-Tain<BR>
